SOME DO'S
• Use single word;
• Avoid confusing words and sentences which are capable of undesirable
construction;
• Do not go for unnecessary repetition;
• Use shorter sentences;
• Express the ideas in clear and fewer words;
• Always use active to the passive voice sentences;
• Choose the right word;
• The meaning of words used should be well known and understood. • Read the whole document carefully and satisfy yourself about the
content, interpretation and the sense it carries. INDIAN PROPERTY SHOW, LONDON
APRIL 2016
